{"title_page": "Fabien Morel", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n[[File:Levine Morel.jpg|thumb|Fabien Morel (right) with [[Marc Levine (mathematician)|Marc Levine]] at the [[Mathematical Research Institute of Oberwolfach|MFO]], 2005]]\n'''Fabien Morel'''  (born 22 January 1965, in [[Reims]]) is a French algebraic geometer and key developer of [[A\u00b9 homotopy theory]] with [[Vladimir Voevodsky]].<ref>{{Citation | last1=Morel | first1=Fabien | last2=Voevodsky | first2=Vladimir | author2-link=Vladimir Voevodsky | title='''A'''<sup>1</sup>-homotopy theory of schemes | url=http://archive.numdam.org/article/PMIHES_1999__90__45_0.pdf | accessdate=9 May 2008 | mr=1813224  | year=1999 | journal=[[Publications Math\u00e9matiques de l'IH\u00c9S]] | issue=90 | pages=45\u2013143 | doi=10.1007/BF02698831 | volume=90}}</ref> Among his accomplishments is the proof of the Friedlander conjecture, and the proof of the complex case of the Milnor conjecture stated in Milnor's 1983 paper 'On the homology of Lie groups made discrete'. This result was presented at the Second Abel Conference, held in January\u2013February 2012.\n\nIn 2006 he was an invited speaker with talk ''A<sup>1</sup>-algebraic topology'' at the [[International Congress of Mathematicians]] in [[Madrid]].<ref>{{cite book|chapter=''A<sup>1</sup>-algebraic topology'' by Fabien Morel|title=Proceedings of the International Congress of Mathematicians, Madrid, 2006|volume=Vol. II|publisher=European Math. Soc.|year=2006|pages=1035\u20131059|url=http://www.icm2006.org/proceedings/Vol_II/contents/ICM_Vol_2_49.pdf}}</ref>\n\n==Selected publications==\n* [https://books.google.com/books?id=fUa5BQAAQBAJ ''A<sup>1</sup>-algebraic topology over a field.''] (= Lecture Notes in Mathematics. 2052). Springer, 2012, {{ISBN|978-3-642-29513-3}}.\n* with [[Marc Levine (mathematician)|Marc Levine]]: [https://books.google.com/books?id=obVAAAAAQBAJ ''Algebraic Cobordism.''] Springer, 2007, {{ISBN|978-3-540-36822-9}}.\n* [https://books.google.com/books?id=LRlWCUfH430C ''Homotopy theory of Schemes.''] American Mathematical Society, 2006 (French original published by [[Soci\u00e9t\u00e9 Math\u00e9matique de France]] 1999)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Morel, Fabien}}\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Reims]]\n[[Category:20th-century French mathematicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century French mathematicians]]\n[[Category:Algebraic geometers]]\n\n\n{{France-mathematician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "[[File:Levine Morel.jpg|thumb|Fabien Morel (right) with [[Marc Levine (mathematician)|Marc Levine]] at the [[Mathematical Research Institute of Oberwolfach|MFO]], 2005]]\n'''Fabien Morel'''  (born 22 January 1965, in [[Reims]]) is a French algebraic geometer and key developer of [[A\u00b9 homotopy theory]] with [[Vladimir Voevodsky]].<ref>{{Citation | last1=Morel | first1=Fabien | last2=Voevodsky | first2=Vladimir | author2-link=Vladimir Voevodsky | title='''A'''<sup>1</sup>-homotopy theory of schemes | url=http://archive.numdam.org/article/PMIHES_1999__90__45_0.pdf | accessdate=9 May 2008 | mr=1813224  | year=1999 | journal=[[Publications Math\u00e9matiques de l'IH\u00c9S]] | issue=90 | pages=45\u2013143 | doi=10.1007/BF02698831 | volume=90}}</ref> Among his accomplishments is the proof of the Friedlander conjecture, and the proof of the complex case of the Milnor conjecture stated in Milnor's 1983 paper 'On the homology of Lie groups made discrete'. This result was presented at the Second Abel Conference, held in January\u2013February 2012.\n\nIn 2006 he was an invited speaker with talk ''A<sup>1</sup>-algebraic topology'' at the [[International Congress of Mathematicians]] in [[Madrid]].<ref>{{cite book|chapter=''A<sup>1</sup>-algebraic topology'' by Fabien Morel|title=Proceedings of the International Congress of Mathematicians, Madrid, 2006|volume=Vol. II|publisher=European Math. Soc.|year=2006|pages=1035\u20131059|url=http://www.icm2006.org/proceedings/Vol_II/contents/ICM_Vol_2_49.pdf}}</ref>\n\n==Selected publications==\n* [https://books.google.com/books/about/A1_Algebraic_Topology_over_a_Field.html?id=fUa5BQAAQBAJ ''A<sup>1</sup>-algebraic topology over a field.''] (= Lecture Notes in Mathematics. 2052). Springer, 2012, {{ISBN|978-3-642-29513-3}}.\n* with [[Marc Levine (mathematician)|Marc Levine]]: [https://books.google.com/books/about/Algebraic_Cobordism.html?id=obVAAAAAQBAJ ''Algebraic Cobordism.''] Springer, 2007, {{ISBN|978-3-540-36822-9}}.\n* [https://books.google.com/books/about/Homotopy_Theory_of_Schemes.html?id=LRlWCUfH430C ''Homotopy theory of Schemes.''] American Mathematical Society, 2006 (French original published by [[Soci\u00e9t\u00e9 Math\u00e9matique de France]] 1999)\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2010}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Morel, Fabien}}\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Reims]]\n[[Category:20th-century French mathematicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century French mathematicians]]\n[[Category:Algebraic geometers]]\n\n\n{{France-mathematician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Dawnseeker2000", "label": "safe", "comment": "minor nitpicking", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fabien_Morel"}
{"title_page": "FCK Rolling Devils", "text_new": "{{infobox basketball club\n| name            = FCK Rolling Devils\n| color1          = <!-- or | colour1 = -->\n| color2          = <!-- or | colour2 = -->\n| logo            =\n| nickname        = Rolling red devils\n| leagues         = Regional league (3rd division)\n| founded         = September 2009\n| dissolved       =\n| history         = \n| arena           = Sports Hall of Schillerschule Kaiserslautern\n| location        = [[Kaiserslautern]]<br />([[Rhineland-Palatinate]], [[Germany]])\n| colors          = Red/White/Black\n| current         = \n| sponsor         = \n| president       = Sascha Gergele\n| coach           = Robin Kaltenbach\n| ownership       = \n| championships   = Regional Cup Winner 2010<br />Regional League Champion 2011<br />2nd Federal League Champion 2014<br />Regional League Champion 2019\n| website         = [http://www.rollingdevils.de/ www.rollingdevils.de]\n| h_body          = C32A28\n| h_pattern_b     = \n| h_shorts        = C32A28\n| h_pattern_s     = \n| a_body          = 000000\n| a_pattern_b     = \n| a_shorts        = 000000\n| a_pattern_s     = \n}}\nThe '''FCK Rolling Devils''' are a [[Wheelchair basketball|wheelchair basketball club]] located in [[Kaiserslautern]] with [[Football in Germany|German soccer club]] [[1. FC Kaiserslautern]] acting as name sponsor. Their first team played in the [[Rollstuhlbasketball-Bundesliga]] from 2014 to 2016 and now plays in the third-class regional league.\n\n== History ==\nThe wheelchair basketball team of 1. FC Kaiserslautern was founded in September 2009 as a part of the club's [[Basketball|basketball department]]. The Rolling Devils entered league play of the German Wheelchair Sports Federation<ref>[http://www.drs.org German Wheelchair Sports Federation (Deutscher Rollstuhl-Sportverband) german homepage] (accessed on March 1, 2014)</ref> in the season 2010/11 on the level of the third-class Regional League (Central Conference). The team won the Regional Cup<ref>[http://www.drs-rollstuhlbasketball.de/index.php?id=43  German Wheelchair Sports Regional Cup (Regionspokal) winners] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131224114315/http://www.drs-rollstuhlbasketball.de/index.php?id=43 |date=2013-12-24 }} (accessed on March 5, 2014)</ref> and advanced to the quarter finals of the German National Cup.<ref>[http://www2.drs-rollstuhlbasketball.de/ligen/showPokal.php?liga=drspokal German Wheelchair Sports Cup (DRS-Pokal) pairings]  (accessed on March 1, 2014)</ref> The Devils finished the season with the championship and promotion to the 2nd German Wheelchair Basketball Federal League (Southern Conference).<ref>[http://www2.drs-rbb.de/ligen/showOverview.php?liga=bl2s 2nd German Wheelchair Basketball Federal League (Southern Conference) (2. Rollstuhlbasketball-Bundesliga S\u00fcd) rankings] (accessed on March 1, 2015)</ref>\n\nIn the next two seasons the Devils dropped from German Wheelchair Sports Cup in the group stage, but finished as runners-up in the 2nd Federal League. In 2013 the team participated for the German Wheelchair Sports Federation in [[International Wheelchair Basketball Federation]] Euroleague 3 and finished in third place.<ref>[http://www.iwbf-europe.org/index.php/news/results/327-results-euroleague-3-2013 IWBF EuroLeague 3 results 2013] (accessed on March 1, 2014)</ref><ref>[http://www.iwbf-europe.org/index.php/eurocup/ranking-clubs IWBF Eurocup club rankings] (accessed on March 1, 2014)</ref>\n\nIn March 2013, FCK Rolling Devils re-established as a separate wheelchair basketball department.<ref>[http://fck.de/en/1-fc-kaiserslautern/fck/structure/departments.html 1.FC Kaiserslautern club departments] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129120412/http://fck.de/en/1-fc-kaiserslautern/fck/structure/departments.html |date=2014-11-29 }} (accessed on March 1, 2014)</ref> In the season 2013/14 the Rolling Devils again advanced to the quarter finals of the German National Cup and in the third attempt won the championship in the 2nd German Federal League thereby gaining promotion to the 1st German Federal League.<ref>[http://www2.drs-rbb.de/ligen/showOverview.php?liga=bl1 1st German Wheelchair Basketball Federal League 2014 (1. Rollstuhlbasketball-Bundesliga) rankings] (accessed on March 1, 2015)</ref> In the season 2014/15, the Devils made it again to the quarter finals of the German National Cup and finished their first season in the 1st German Federal League on rank 7 and thereby as the best promoted team of the last four seasons.\n\nIn July 2015, the spin-off of FCK Rolling Devils as independent club with 1.FC Kaiserslautern acting as name sponsor took place. The wheelchair basketball department at 1.FC Kaiserslautern was suspended at the annual general meeting of the club in December 2015. In the season 2015/16, the Devils again made it to the quarter finals of the German National Cup and finished the season on rank 7.\n\nIn August 2016, the club withdrew its first team from the 1st German Federal League for financial and sports reasons and continued league play with their second team in the third-class regional league. In the next two seasons, the Rolling Devils finished on rank 3. In the season 2018/19, the Devils won the championship and right for promotion to the 2nd German Wheelchair Basketball Federal League (Southern Conference), but decided to stay in the regional league for financial reasons. The season 2019/20 ended ahead of schedule because of the [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]] and the Rolling Devils finished with several games less played than the other teams on rank 4.\n\n== Honors ==\n\n===National===\n* Regional Cup (Central Conference) Winner 2010\n* Regional League (Central Conference) Champion 2011 (''Regionalliga Mitte'', 3rd division)\n* 2nd Federal League (Southern Conference) Champion 2014\n* Regional League (Central Conference) Champion 2019 (''Regionalliga Mitte'', 3rd division)\n\n===2nd team===\n* First League (Central Conference) Champion 2014 (''Oberliga Mitte'', 4th division)\n* Regional Cup (Central Conference) Winner 2014\n\n== Players ==\n\n=== Roster 2020/21 ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|- style=\"background-color:#ABCDEF;\"\n! Number\n! Name\n! Nationality\n! Year of birth\n! [[Wheelchair basketball#Classifications|Classification]]\n! [[Basketball#Positions|Position]]\n! In the club since\n! Former club\n|}\n\n=== Leaves 2020 ===\n\n== Season by season ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|- style=\"background-color:#ABCDEF;\"\n! Season\n! League\n! Position (Teams)\n! W\n! D\n! L\n! Points\n! Baskets\n! National cup competitions\n! International competitions\n|- style=\"background-color:#B9FFC5;\"\n| 2010/11 || Regional league (Central conference) || 1 (8) || 14 || 0 || 0 || 28:0 || 1228:428 || Regional Cup: Winner<br />German Cup: quarter finals ||\n|-\n| 2011/12 || 2nd Federal League (Southern conference) || 2 (8) || 11 || 0 || 3 || 22:6 || 961:767 || German Cup: group stage ||\n|-\n| 2012/13 || 2nd Federal League (Southern conference) || 2 (8) || 10 || 0 || 4 || 20:8 || 908:764 || German Cup: group stage || IWBF EuroLeague 3: Position 3\n|- style=\"background-color:#B9FFC5;\"\n| 2013/14 || 2nd Federal League (Southern conference) || 1 (8) || 14 || 0 || 0 || 28:0 || 1050:692 || German Cup: quarter finals ||\n|-\n| 2014/15 || 1st Federal League || 7 (10) || 6 || 0 || 12 || 12:24 || 1042:1195 || German Cup: quarter finals ||\n|-\n| 2015/16 || 1st Federal League || 7 (10) || 7 || 0 || 11 || 14:22 || 1206:1300 || German Cup: quarter finals ||\n|- style=\"background-color:#FFCBCB;\"\n| 2016/17 || 1st Federal League || 10 (10) || 0 || 0 || 18 || 0:36 || 0:360 || ||\n|-\n| 2016/17 || Regional league (Central conference)* || 3(11) || 15 || 0 || 5 || 30:10 || 1082:763 || ||\n|-\n| 2017/18 || Regional league (Central conference) || 3(7) || 11 || 0 || 5 || 22:10 || 952:817 || ||\n|- style=\"background-color